item.title: Danielle add a quote by Edgar Allan Poe
item.description: "All that we see or seem is but a dream within a dream." -- Edgar Allan Poe

item.title: Danielle add a quote by Søren Kierkegaard
item.description: "If anyone on the verge of action should judge himself according to the outcome, he would never begin." -- Søren Kierkegaard

item.title: Danielle add a quote by Niccolo Machiavelli
item.description: "A prudent man should always follow in the path trodden by great men and imitate those who are most excellent, so that if he does not attain to their greatness, at any rate he will get some tinge of it." -- Niccolo Machiavelli

item.title: Danielle add a quote by George Orwell
item.description: "He who controls the past controls the future. He who controls the present controls the past." -- George Orwell

item.title: Danielle add a quote by Aleksandr I. Solzhenitsyn
item.description: "The meaning of earthly existence lies not, as we have grown used to thinking, in prospering but in the development of the soul." -- Aleksandr I. Solzhenitsyn
